<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-69-0767 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Alwyn North Field, due to come on stream by the end of 1987, is acombination of a gas field and an oil field. Offshore facilities aredesigned to handle 9 MMSCM/D of gas and 100,000 BOPD of oil, in a highlyintegrated process scheme which links oil and gas exports. Natural andassociated gases are combined offshore for treatment, compression, meteringand injection into the Frigg gas transport system which takes gas tothe St. Fergus onshore terminal. This terminal originally designed forFrigg gas mainly, had to be modified to accept new gas from Alwyn andmaintain the sales gas within specifications.</TEXT></DOC>